<% help_title "Help on #{ PcpCategory.model_name.human }" %>
  <div class="container">
    <%= helpcrumbs %>
    <%= help_header %>
    <p class="lead">Create and Maintain Observation/Response Log (PCP) Categories</p>
    <h3>Introduction</h3>
    <p>An PCP Category represents the agreement between two project groups to participate in a
      process where an PCP Subject (e.g. a document or a site) presented by the
      <%= help_term PcpCategory.human_attribute_name( :p_grour_id )-%> to the 
      <%= help_term PcpCategory.human_attribute_name( :c_group_id )-%> for review and comments.</p>
    <p>PCP Categories are thus used to group Observation/Response Logs having the same kind of subjects and
      the same originating and receiving project groups. For example, all reviews of project 
      documents by the client's organisation would be one PCP Category; another PCP Category would be all
      reviews of civil works documents by the systems groups; again another PCP Category would be all
      internal reviews within a group.</p>
    <p>The following attributes are administered per category:</p>
    <ul>
      <li><%= help_param PcpCategory.human_attribute_name( :id ) -%> is the unique identifier of each 
        individual PCP Category.</li>
      <li><%= help_param PcpCategory.human_attribute_name( :label ) -%> is the name of the PCP Category.
        The link here will lead to all PCP Subjects within this PCP Category.</li>
      <li><%= help_param PcpCategory.human_attribute_name( :c_group_id ) -%> is the project group providing 
        comments and observations on the PCP Subjects in this PCP Category.</li>
      <li><%= help_param PcpCategory.human_attribute_name( :p_group_id ) -%> is the project group presenting
        the PCP Subjects to be reviewed and commented on. This is group also provides the responses to
        any observations and comments.</li>
      <li><%= help_param PcpCategory.human_attribute_name( :c_owner_id )-%> is the default owner for
        the <%= help_term PcpCategory.human_attribute_name( :c_grour_id )-%> for any
        new PCP Subjects in this PCP Category. This parameter is required to ensure that there is always
        an owner defined for any PCP Subject.</li>
      <li><%= help_param PcpCategory.human_attribute_name( :p_owner_id )-%> is the default owner for
        the <%= help_term PcpCategory.human_attribute_name( :p_grour_id )-%> for any
        new PCP Subjects in this PCP Category. This parameter is required to ensure that there is always
        an owner defined for any PCP Subject.</li>
      <li><%= help_param PcpCategory.human_attribute_name( :c_deputy_id )-%> can be used to define a
        default deputy for the <%= help_term PcpCategory.human_attribute_name( :c_owner_id )-%>.
      <li><%= help_param PcpCategory.human_attribute_name( :p_deputy_id )-%> can be used to define a
        default deputy for the <%= help_term PcpCategory.human_attribute_name( :p_owner_id )-%>.
    </ul>
    <p>Any accounts (owner or deputy) must have the necessary permissions for their respective group 
      to manage the PCP Subjects in this PCP Category.</p>
    <%= help_footer FEATURE_ID_PCP_CATEGORIES %>
  </div> <!-- /container -->

